==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: To-day
<hw>To-day"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>t⟦omac⟧
d⟦ae⟧g</ets>. See <er>To</er>, <pos>prep.</pos>, and
<er>Day</er>.]</ety> <def>On this day; on the present day.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Worcester's horse came but <qex>to-day</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>To-day</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: To-day
<hw>To-day"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The present day.</def> <-- usu.
spelt <asp>today.</asp> -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On <qex>to-day</qex>⟦br⟧
Is worth for me a thousand yesterdays.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- today adj. modern, recent. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toddle</ent>⟦br⟧
